esponding object, then use its -&gt;cpuset.<br><br>If physical, you just need a cpuset that contains the bit corresponding to this id. You can use hwloc_bitmap_only(set, &lt;id&gt;) to reset a (previously allocated) cpuset to nothing but this id.<br><br>Brice<br><br><br><br>Le 18/08/2011 10:10, PULVERAIL Sébastien a écrit&nbsp;: <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Hi,<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>I&#8217;m looking for a function that allows to bind the current thread to a specific cpu given by its id.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>I found the function hwloc_set_thread_cpubind to bind a thread to a cpuset.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>I also found the function hwloc_bitmap_singlify to keep only one index in the cpuset.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>But I didn&#8217;t found anything to only keep the cpu I need in my cpuset&#8230;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><br>Is it possible&nbsp;? <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style='color:#1F497D'>--<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:8.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:gray'>Seb</span><span style='color:gray'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><pre><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></pre><pre><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></pre><pre>_______________________________________________<o:p></o:p></pre><pre>hwloc-users mailing list<o:p></o:p></pre><pre><a href="mailto:hwloc-users@open-mpi.org">hwloc-users@open-mpi.org</a><o:p></o:p></pre><pre><a href="http://www.open-mpi.org/mailman/listinfo.cgi/hwloc-users">http://www.open-mpi.org/mailman/listinfo.cgi/hwloc-users</a><o:p></o:p></pre><p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p></div></body></html>
